How does cassie figure out votes then - does it look for the start of a string or any unique string in the middle of a username? (Eg would [vote mugvi] work for Smugvid as well? (I noticed people voting for "knight" and rorab even though they have "the" in their usernames)
I don't 100% understand it but my understanding is that it is based on the analysis of Trigrams, which wiki has a very bare article about.
And then it has an alogrithm that compares various trigrams and if the result is unique enough, it processes the vote
It can also handle mispellings because of it

But it isn't the way a human would think about it, so funny things come up like this: my username is Tfang an my sister's is FaleohFang. I long predate her, and for about a year and a half, everyone just called me and voted for me by "Fang"
And because I'm Tfang, it was easy to think of her as "FFang"
Except  that because of how trigrams work out, [vote Fang] would vote for her, as it matches the way her name breaks down into 3's better, and [vote FFang] would get ME for the same reason.
So a lot of middle-of-name votes work as long as there is high uniqueness, which the_rorab and theknightofcups have
But it took some experimentation to figure out what it would accept if ZenMonkey and Zenofkermit were both in a game - and it is basically the whole end of their names

The reason you don't actually see us do things like [vote mugvi], even though I can't think of a roster where it wouldn't work, is that we feel votes should be HUMAN readable as well on a glance so everyone has true information. =)
